cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on cross-lingual transfer for syntactic analysis tasks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a generative model with a structured prior and employs an invertible projection to learn a new interlingual latent embedding space, which involves techniques from machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses regularization and joint learning to improve the transfer performance, which is a common technique in optimization and neural network training, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
